The paper explores the dynamics of image virality in an online social network, which involves analyzing visual characteristics of images and their impact on user reactions. This falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), as well as Multimedia (cs.MM) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) due to the use of image analysis techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses potential user behavior and preferences, which relates to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Statistical Learning (cs.SD).
